{
  "stem": "9446.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It took us a couple days to prepare ourselves for some sort of an exodus.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now my father was very much concerned with my life, because the young people-- I wasn't even 20 years old at the time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was 20 years minus 12 days, because the war started on the 1st, and my birthday's September 12.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So my father wanted me to get out from Warsaw as quick as possible to save my life.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And on the six days-- sixth day of Warsaw, hundreds of thousands-- sixth day of-- sixth day of war, sorry-- hundreds of thousands of Jews were running away from Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The Germans were approaching already Warsaw, very close, and trying-- trying to go away as far as possible to the eastern part of Poland.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because, you know, Germany was on the western [? part-- ?] the western side of Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were approaching to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So all of us were trying to get away, ran away from.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So you could see thousands-- hundreds of thousands of people marching, towards the eastern border of between Poland and Russia.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Now this was another day which I will never forget.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were approached-- we approached a town in this march towards the east-- eastern part of Poland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was a town under a River Bug, B-U-G-- a town by the name Malkinia, M-A-L-K-I-N-I-A.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And-- and that town-- that town was like a borderline between the Russians and the Germans.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now the Russians wouldn't let us in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were screaming, you know, hollering at us in Russian [NON-ENGLISH], which means go back, go back.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Who wanted to go back?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Going back is like going to commit suicide.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they didn't care.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we were sitting there, and it was already cold-- almost October, something like that.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
